# IUUT Governance — Cursor Rules

This repository is governed by a binding multi-agent contract. **Before any code action**, you (the Cursor agent) must consult:

1. `AGENTS.md` (repo root) — the universal contract.
2. `.agent/CONSTITUTION.md` — articles I–X, immutable.
3. `.agent/SCOPE_GUARDRAILS.md` — what you can and cannot do.
4. `.agent/AGENT_WORKFLOW.md` — the ritual.
5. `.agent/HANDOFF_PROTOCOL.md` — commit/PR conventions.
6. `.agent/DEFINITION_OF_DONE.md` — acceptance bar.
7. `.agent/CODE_STYLE.md`, `.agent/SECURITY_PROTOCOL.md`, `.agent/TESTING_CONTRACT.md` for code tasks.

## Hard rules (summary; full normative text in `.agent/CONSTITUTION.md`)

**Must:**
- Add `Agent: cursor/<version>` and `Consulted: <doc>#<section>` trailers to every commit.
- Round-trip parser changes against a fixture.
- Backup → write → re-parse → restore-on-failure for save-file mutators.
- Anonymize fixtures (no real Steam IDs, character names, paths).
- Preserve unknown JSON fields on round-trip (forward compatibility).
- Update the spec when you change behavior the spec describes.

**Must not:**
- Add telemetry, cloud upload, auth, or any unenumerated network call.
- Hardcode usernames, paths, Steam IDs, character names.
- Bypass the `commit-msg` hook without a `Governance-Override:` trailer.
- Amend `.agent/CONSTITUTION.md` outside the amendment process.
- Mark a task complete when tests fail.

## When stuck

Stop. Do not guess. Per `.agent/SCOPE_GUARDRAILS.md` §3: surface the contradiction, name the two interpretations, ask the human.

## Reference docs (the spec you implement against)

- `docs/IUUT-PROJECT-DOCUMENTATION.md` — master spec.
- `Icarus-Analysis.md` — save-format field guide.

Other agents (Claude Code, OpenAI Codex, Google Antigravity) operate here too. Read their commit trailers; respect their style; do not silently introduce a third pattern.
